&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Position:&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;nbsp; Biotech Program Manager&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Location:&lt;/strong&gt; South San Francisco&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Type:&lt;/strong&gt; Full-time&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;hr&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Ohalo is hiring a&amp;nbsp;&lt;strong&gt;Biotech Program Manager (PM)&lt;/strong&gt; to lead one or several discovery, development, or production programs. You will manage and oversee programs focused on discovering molecules, or developing transformation or acceleration techniques, working at the molecular, cellular, and whole plant levels.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This is a full-accountability leadership role: you will act as the general manager for a set of breakthrough technology programs, owning outcomes, defining strategy, and managing the work of cross-functional individuals from science, engineering, and operations.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will be responsible for setting deliverables, assigning work, developing and updating timelines, and ensuring on-time delivery of outcomes.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This role requires a candidate who is competent with molecular or cellular biology or biochemistry (but is not necessarily a plant scientist), has experience designing, developing, and managing high throughput and automated lab workflows, has strong leadership and organizational skills, and is very capable and proven in leveraging AI tools to accelerate and scale work output.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The ideal person thrives in a high-ownership, fast-moving environment and is excited by leading breakthrough scientific discovery efforts.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;hr&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Responsibilities:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Program General Management &amp;amp; Accountability&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Own &lt;strong&gt;program success&lt;/strong&gt; for one or more programs focused on discovery, process development, or production workstreams.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Design high throughput and other technology-led methods for screening, discovery, and process engineering.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Drive alignment across stakeholders and executive leadership and ensure crisp decision-making, escalation, and accountability.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Own budgeting, forecasting, and analytics of managed programs.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Cross-Functional Orchestration &amp;amp; Execution, Communications&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Build and maintain integrated program plans that connect complex biological systems with, for example, hardware and software systems, ensuring dependencies and critical paths are explicit and managed.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Define program architecture at the “system level” (workstreams, interfaces, handoffs, validation strategy), and ensure teams execute to an integrated schedule.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Lead execution across science, engineering, lab and greenhouse operations, —coordinating interdependent projects into a single coherent program plan.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Directly manage and drive execution of cross functional program team members.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Proactively identify bottlenecks and unblock teams through clear prioritization, fast follow-through, and structured problem-solving.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Create clear communication artifacts for diverse audiences—from technical deep dives to executive summaries.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Tech- and AI-Led Program Management&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Use modern tooling—including AI—to accelerate planning, synthesis, execution, communication and documentation.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Promote practical AI adoption within the program team (e.g., structured decision logs, automated status synthesis, faster technical writing), while maintaining high standards for accuracy and traceability.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;hr&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;&l

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Position:&lt;/strong&gt; Business Development Lead&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Location:&lt;/strong&gt; South San Francisco, CA&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Type:&lt;/strong&gt; Full-time&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;br&gt;The Opportunity:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Ohalo™ is seeking a Business Development Lead to source, structure, and close the partnerships that bring our agriculture products to market worldwide. This is a deal-driving role at its core. You will build and own relationships across the supply chain — growers, packers and shippers, processors, distributors, and retail/QSR buyers — and convert them into revenue-generating commercial agreements. You will be the commercial face of Ohalo in the field, moving partnerships from first conversation to signed deal to scaled execution, in close collaboration with breeding, commercial, and regulatory teams.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;As Ohalo expands into new regions, you will also help shape where and how we enter — identifying the right partners, mapping the value chain, and building the strategic roadmap for markets where we don&#39;t yet have a playbook.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This is a high-impact role for a self-starting operator who thrives on ownership and execution. You will succeed if you are relationship-driven and persuasive, relentless about moving deals forward, and equally at home in a grower&#39;s field, a processor&#39;s boardroom, and an internal cross-functional huddle.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;br&gt;Areas of Key Responsibilities:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Business Development &amp;amp; Supply Chain Partnerships&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Source, negotiate, and close strategic, revenue-generating partnerships across the supply chain — growers, packers and shippers, processors, distributors, and retail/QSR buyers.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Build and own durable relationships with commercial partners, serving as Ohalo&#39;s primary commercial point of contact from first outreach through signed agreement.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Drive deals end to end: structure terms, align internal stakeholders, and steward agreements through to execution and scale.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Serve as a key commercial face of Ohalo in global markets, representing our product vision directly to external stakeholders, growers, and customers.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Build the commercial alliances that secure demand and route Ohalo&#39;s portfolio through the value chain to end customers.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Strategic Roadmap &amp;amp; Partner Identification — New Expansion Regions&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Build the analytical backbone for commercial decisions — run market sizing and pricing analysis that informs priority markets, which partners to pursue, how to structure terms, and where Ohalo&#39;s portfolio commands premium value.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;For new and emerging markets, identify and prioritize the partners, segments, and value-chain entry points that unlock commercial traction.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Build the strategic roadmap for regions where Ohalo lacks an established playbook, mapping grower economics, processor demand, and downstream value-chain incentives well enough to enter with conviction.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Develop focused business cases and entry plans for new product introductions, sizing the opportunity and sequencing the partner approach.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Where a region is new, shape the volume and adoption assumptions and coordinate launch readiness enough to align supply availability and partner enablement, drawing on field trial data and partner pipeline intelligence.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;br&gt;Qualifications:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;5+ years of experience in business development, commercial strategy, or sales in the agricultural industry, with a track record of pers

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Position Title: &lt;/strong&gt;Commercial Potato Breeder&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Location:&lt;/strong&gt; Watsonville, CA with 25-50% travel&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Type: &lt;/strong&gt;Full-time&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;br&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Opportunity:&lt;/strong&gt; &lt;br&gt;Ohalo is seeking a &lt;strong&gt;Commercial Potato Breeder &lt;/strong&gt;to lead the advancement of potato varieties from late-stage development through commercial readiness. This role sits at the intersection of breeding, agronomy, and commercial execution, ensuring new varieties perform consistently across environments and meet the needs of growers, processors, and partners. This person works closely to align our product direction and production efforts with the needs and successful results of our growers.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The ideal candidate combines strong technical expertise in potato variety development with a practical, field-oriented mindset and the ability to collaborate closely with internal R&amp;amp;D teams and external stakeholders.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Key Responsibilities&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Lead &lt;strong&gt;late-stage variety development&lt;/strong&gt; activities for potato programs, including multi-location field trials and pre-commercial evaluations that align with the Ohalo commercial go-to-market strategy.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Design, execute, and analyze &lt;strong&gt;regional and on-farm trials&lt;/strong&gt; to validate performance, stability, and agronomic fit.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Serve as the technical bridge between &lt;strong&gt;R&amp;amp;D, product, and commercial teams&lt;/strong&gt;, translating data into clear deliverables.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Own the product registration &amp;amp; UPOV process in a global landscape.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Partner with growers, processors, and other external collaborators to support trial execution and feedback to support and drive commercial sales and vision.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Collect, synthesize, and communicate trial results to internal stakeholders in a clear, actionable way.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Evaluate varieties against &lt;strong&gt;commercial benchmarks&lt;/strong&gt; (yield, quality, disease resistance, storage, processing traits, etc.).&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Provide technical input into &lt;strong&gt;variety positioning, launch planning, and market segmentation &lt;/strong&gt;as it aligns with our commercial organization.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Support continuous improvement of Ohalo’s variety development and evaluation processes.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Qualifications&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Master’s degree or higher in Agronomy, Plant Science, Horticulture, Crop Science, or a related field.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;5+ years of direct experience in &lt;strong&gt;potato variety development, agronomy, or commercial seed systems.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Hands-on experience designing and managing &lt;strong&gt;field trials across multiple environments.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Familiarity with production-scale constraints and process control (sampling plans, SOP validation, QC thresholds).&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Strong understanding of potato production&lt;/strong&gt; systems, grower needs, and commercial success factors.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Excellent communication skills&lt;/strong&gt;. Ability to interpret agronomic and performance data and translate it into commercial insights.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Comfortable working in a fast-moving, fluid, collaborative, and innovative environment.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Willingness to travel&lt;/strong&gt; as needed to trial sites and partner locations. Travel amount will vary depending on activities for the timing of the year i.e. planting, harvesting, etc. (10%-50%).&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;H

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Position:&lt;/strong&gt; &amp;nbsp;Executive Assistant to the President &amp;amp; Chief Operating Officer (COO)&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Location: &lt;/strong&gt;South San Francisco&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Type: &lt;/strong&gt;Full-time&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;br&gt;The Opportunity&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Ohalo™ is seeking a dedicated, highly organized &lt;strong&gt;Executive Assistant to the President &amp;amp; Chief Operating Officer (COO)&lt;/strong&gt;. This is an execution-focused, high-velocity support role for a true administrative partner.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will be our COO’s “right-hand person,” enabling them to advance company initiatives and goals. By managing complex calendar logistics and filtering incoming administrative demands, you will ensure the COO can focus entirely on high-level leadership and strategy.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;In our fast-growing environment, you will establish steady administrative routines, navigate complex scheduling dynamics, and ensure the COO&#39;s schedule and travel are always one step ahead of a rapidly expanding business.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This is a high-impact role for a self-starting assistant who thrives on organization, execution, and discretion. You will approach the COO’s professional and personal logistics holistically, fiercely protecting their time and focus. You will succeed if you are relationship-driven, solutions-oriented, and equally at home managing fluid calendars as you are rolling up your sleeves for ad-hoc personal tasks.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;br&gt;What You’ll Do&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;h4&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Executive &amp;amp; Calendar Support&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h4&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strategically design and own the COO’s calendar. Schedule and prioritize meetings, protect focus time, and skillfully handle competing demands across internal and external stakeholders.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Manage end-to-end travel logistics, including flights, lodging, ground transport, and detailed itineraries for the COO and broader commercial team as needed.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Help the COO keep momentum by tracking action items, key decisions, and commitments coming out of commercial and operational meetings to ensure steady follow-through.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Organize digital files, coordinate meeting prep materials, and ensure the COO is fully briefed and prepared for the day ahead&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h4&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Office and Event Operations&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h4&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Act as the primary, welcoming point of contact for visitors, external partners, and clients arriving for meetings with the COO.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Partner closely with the rest of the administrative team to coordinate logistics for company offsites, board meetings, commercial partner visits, and other key corporate events.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Provide seamless backup coverage for the office manager during absences or when business needs require temporary support.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Personal Assistant Support&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Handle personal scheduling, private travel arrangements, and ad-hoc personal tasks to completely optimize the COO&#39;s daily productivity&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Exercise impeccable judgment and strict confidentiality when handling highly sensitive professional and personal information.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;br&gt;What We’re Looking For&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Experience:&lt;/strong&gt; 4+ years of experience as an Executive Assistant supporting C-suite or senior operations leaders, ideally within a fast-paced, high-growth environment.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Business Acumen:&lt;/strong&gt; A strong foundational understanding of corporate operations; you recognize who key stakeholders, clients, and partners are, a

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Position Title: &lt;/strong&gt;Field Technical Development Lead&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Location:&lt;/strong&gt; Watsonville, CA or Bakersfield, CA (with 25-50% travel)&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Type: &lt;/strong&gt;Full-time&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Reports into&lt;/strong&gt;: Breeding&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;hr&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;strong&gt;Opportunity:&lt;/strong&gt; Ohalo has developed the world’s first true hybrid potato seed system using its proprietary Boosted Breeding platform. This unprecedented advancement unlocks a step-change in potato farming, giving growers the ability to move from seed potato to true seed. Successful deployment of true seed requires rigorous variety testing alongside agronomic systems development.&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Ohalo is seeking a &lt;strong&gt;Field Tech Dev Lead &lt;/strong&gt;to support the development of hybrid true potato seed varieties from late-stage breeding through commercial readiness. Responsibilities include coordinating agronomic system development for planting, fertility, and crop protection with grower partners, coordinating field trials and early commercial trials across the US, data gathering and implementation of data collection systems, and feedback and support of grower partners and the broader Ohalo potato breeding organization.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The ideal candidate combines strong technical expertise in agronomic systems development with a detail-oriented approach to trial design and data gathering, and service-oriented approach to working with grower partners.&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;hr&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Key Responsibilities&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Design, execute, and analyze &lt;strong&gt;regional and on-farm trials&lt;/strong&gt; to validate performance, stability, and agronomic fit of new true seed hybrids.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Design and test multivariate &lt;strong&gt;agronomic systems&lt;/strong&gt; to optimize in-field performance of new true seed hybrids.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ensure &lt;strong&gt;robust data gathering&lt;/strong&gt; of commercial and breeding field trials.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Support grower partners throughout field and commercial trials with in-field agronomic planning, in-season data gathering, and post-harvest phenotyping and data collection.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Serve as the technical bridge between &lt;strong&gt;breeding and commercial teams&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Provide technical input into &lt;strong&gt;variety positioning, launch planning, and market adoption, &lt;/strong&gt;leveraging insights from trials to deliver field-ready agronomic recommendations.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;hr&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Qualifications&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Master’s degree or higher in Agronomy, Plant Science, Horticulture, Crop Science, or a related field.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;5+ years of direct experience coordinating agronomic systems and methods testing and deployment&lt;strong&gt;.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Hands-on experience designing and managing &lt;strong&gt;field trials across multiple environments.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Familiarity with production-scale constraints and process control (sampling plans, SOP validation, QC thresholds).&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Highly organized and data-oriented&lt;/strong&gt; with a strong capacity for building standardized and scalable methods for data collection and grower communication.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Excellent communication skills&lt;/strong&gt;. Ability to interpret agronomic and performance data and translate it into insights and documentation.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Comfortable working in a fast-moving, fluid, collaborative, and innovative environment.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Willingness to travel&lt;/strong&gt; as needed to trial sites

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Position Title:&lt;/strong&gt; Greenhouse Technician&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Location: &lt;/strong&gt;Watsonville, CA&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Time Type:&lt;/strong&gt; Full Time&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;em&gt;The Opportunity:&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Ohalo is seeking candidates with a passion for hands-on work growing plants to join our greenhouse team. Greenhouse Technicians will produce beautiful, healthy plants to support a team of scientists who seek to revolutionize plant breeding. Job responsibilities include planting, transplanting, watering, scouting for pests and disease, weeding, data collection, seed harvesting and processing, and performing controlled pollinations. The successful candidate will be safety-aware, efficient, reliable, and responsible. The candidate must also be willing and able to perform repetitive physical tasks such as potting and planting within the greenhouse. Previous greenhouse or field experience is beneficial, but not required.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;em&gt;Responsibilities:&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Daily care and upkeep of multiple species of plants&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Interact with scientists to accurately collect and record data using an electronic notebook&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Scouting for and manually removing pests and weeds, as well as applying beneficial insects to control pests&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Pesticide applications, reporting, and record keeping&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Prepare media for planting, plant or transplant seeds, cuttings, and other propagules&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Monitor and adjust irrigation, nutrient, lighting and climate to optimize plant health&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Harvest, process, record, and organize seed&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Maintain a clean and safe work environment&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Maintain security of company information including trade secrets&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Candidate Profile:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Basic knowledge of plant science, horticulture and plant materials, propagation, and pest management&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ability to collaborate with diverse and creative teams&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ability to problem solve and find solutions&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Detail oriented and takes a proactive approach to routine tasks&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ability to lift 50 pounds&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ability to perform repetitive tasks for several hours&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Must be able to work weekends&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ability to hold a California driver’s license and potential to be covered by a company vehicle insurance plan&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;Below is the pay range for this position that we reasonably expect to pay. Individual compensation is based on various factors including experience, education, skillset, and other relevant qualifications. This ran&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;ge is for the Watsonville, CA location and may be adjusted to the labor market in other geographic areas.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;Anticipated compensation: $24-$27/hr&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About Ohalo:&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Ohalo™ aims to accelerate evolution to unlock nature&#39;s potential. Founded in 2019, Ohalo develops novel breeding systems and improved plant varieties that help farmers grow more food with fewer natural resources, increasing the yield, resiliency, and genetic diversity of crops to sustainably feed our population. Ohalo&#39;s breakthrough technology, Boosted Breeding™, will usher in a new era of improved productivity to radically transform global agriculture. For

