&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Position Title: &lt;/strong&gt;Program Manager&lt;br&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Location: &lt;/strong&gt;South San Francisco, CA&lt;br&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Type: &lt;/strong&gt;Full-time&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Ohalo is hiring a Program Manager (PM) to lead strategic programs across the organization. You will manage and oversee cross-functional programs that span R&amp;amp;D, engineering, and operations, driving complex initiatives from concept through execution and delivery.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This is a full-accountability leadership role: you will act as the general manager for a set of high-impact programs, owning outcomes, defining strategy, and managing the work of cross-functional individuals across technical and business functions.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This role requires&amp;nbsp; strong program and project management fundamentals, experience leading complex cross-functional initiatives, strong leadership and organizational skills, and proven ability to leverage AI tools to accelerate and scale work output. Experience in a technical, scientific, or engineering environment is a plus but not required.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The ideal person thrives in a high-ownership, fast-moving environment and is excited by leading complex, high-stakes initiatives from ambiguity to execution.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Responsibilities:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Program General Management &amp;amp; Accountability&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Own program success for one or more strategic, cross-functional programs.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Design and implement scalable processes and methods for planning, execution, and tracking.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Drive alignment across stakeholders and executive leadership and own crisp decision-making, escalation, and accountability.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Own budgeting, forecasting, and analytics of managed programs.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Cross-Functional Orchestration &amp;amp; Execution, Communications&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Build and maintain integrated program plans that connect complex, interdependent workstreams across teams and disciplines, ensuring dependencies and critical paths are explicit and managed.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Define program architecture at the “system level” (workstreams, interfaces, handoffs, validation strategy), and ensure teams execute to an integrated schedule.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Make the call on trade-offs and escalations; drive alignment across scientists, operators, and executive leadership without waiting for consensus.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Proactively identify bottlenecks and unblock teams through clear prioritization, fast follow-through, and structured problem-solving.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Translate technical complexity into clear artifacts for audiences ranging from scientists to Ohalo’s board&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Use AI tools as a working practice to accelerate your work and move faster than a traditional PM function, while holding a high bar for accuracy and traceability.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Qualifications:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;6-8+ years experience leading complex, cross-functional programs or portfolios (R&amp;amp;D, technology, operations, or related), with clear accountability for outcomes.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong systems thinker, comfortable operating across disciplines and synthesizing ambiguity into executable plans.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Demonstrated ability to manage cross-functional teams and deliver against timelines, milestones, and stakeholder commitments typical of program management roles.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Proven ability to influence without authority, negotiate tradeoffs, and create alignment across technical and non-technical stakeholders.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;High ownership, intrinsically motivated leader who is energized by mission-driven work and holds a high bar for follow-through.&lt;/li&gt;
